   "source": [
    "# Environment Functional Testing — Issue #33\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective:** Verify complete environment functionality by testing `reset()`, `step()`, and `render()`, running multiple episodes using random actions, and logging observations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "a3d6f14c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Current working directory: c:\\Dynamic_pricing_ rl\\dynamic-pricing-rl\\notebooks\n",
      "Import successful!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), '..', 'pricing_env'))\n",
    "from pricing_env import PricingEnv\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Current working directory:\", os.getcwd())\n",
    "print(\"Import successful!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b6c887ec",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Test 1: `reset()`\n",
    "\n",
    "Create the environment and reset it. It should return the starting state `[inventory, days_left]`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "6b7ab625",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initial state: [100, 30]\n",
      "reset() PASSED\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "env = PricingEnv(initial_inventory=100, total_days=30)\n",
    "\n",
    "state = env.reset()\n",
    "print(\"Initial state:\", state)\n",
    "\n",
    "assert state == [100, 30], \"reset() did not return the expected initial state!\"\n",
    "print(\"reset() PASSED\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c10d00ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Test 2: `step()`\n",
    "\n",
    "Take a single pricing action and check that the environment returns a valid next_state, reward, done flag, and info dict."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "7dd53374",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Next state: [96, 29]\n",
      "Reward: 1600\n",
      "Done: False\n",
      "Info: {'price': 400, 'units_sold': 4}\n",
      "step() PASSED\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "action = 2  # pick a price level index (e.g. index 2 in price_levels list)\n",
    "\n",
    "next_state, reward, done, info = env.step(action)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Next state:\", next_state)\n",
    "print(\"Reward:\", reward)\n",
    "print(\"Done:\", done)\n",
    "print(\"Info:\", info)\n",
    "\n",
    "assert isinstance(next_state, list) and len(next_state) == 2, \"next_state should be [inventory, days_left]\"\n",
    "assert isinstance(reward, (int, float)), \"reward should be a number\"\n",
    "assert isinstance(done, bool), \"done should be a boolean\"\n",
    "print(\"step() PASSED\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8420f82a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Test 3: `render()`\n",
    "\n",
    "Check that render() prints the current state without errors."
   ]
  },
